# One Responsibility Per Function

Prefer multiple functions over a single function that takes a parameter to change its behavior. Each function should do one thing.

## Avoid

```rust
// BAD: one function, behavior selected by enum
fn update_region_to(&self, region: ..., dest: &mut Grid2d<u8>, merge: CostmapMerge);
// call: grid.update_region_to(r, dest, CostmapMerge::Overwrite);
```

## Prefer

```rust
// GOOD: separate functions, clear names
fn copy_region_to(&self, min: UVec2, max: UVec2, dest: &mut Grid2d<u8>);
fn merge_region_max_to(&self, min: UVec2, max: UVec2, dest: &mut Grid2d<u8>);
// call: grid.copy_region_to(r.min, r.max, dest);
```

## Why

- Call sites are clearer: `update_overwrite()` vs `update(UpdateType::Overwrite)`.
- Easier to discover and document each behavior.
- No need to pass or document a "mode" enum for a single call.

